            <h5 class="font-bold text-emerald-900 mb-2">Cheque Bounce (138 NI Act)</h5>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-7 text-[15px]"> Cases under Section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act arise when a cheque is returned unpaid due to insufficient funds or other legally recognised reasons, requiring prompt legal steps. </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-7 text-[15px] mt-2"> Our team assists in issuing statutory notices, filing complaints, representing clients during trial, and advising on settlement or compounding options wherever legally appropriate. </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-7 text-[15px] mt-2"> We represent both complainants and accused persons, focusing on procedural accuracy, proper documentation, and a practical legal approach throughout the matter. </p>
         </div>
         <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[22px] border-l-[6px] border-emerald-600 shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-2 hover:shadow-2xl transition h-full"> 
